## Citation Requirements

If you use this software and the underlying datasets in your research, please cite:

**This Work**:
```bibtex
@software{promptgfm_bio,
  author = {Yash Verma},
  title = {PromptGFM-Bio: A Prompt-Conditioned Graph Foundation Model for Rare Disease Gene Prediction},
  year = {2026},
  url = {https://github.com/pes1ug23am910/PromptGFM-Bio}
}
```

**STRING Database**:
```bibtex
@article{string2023,
  title={The STRING database in 2023: protein–protein association networks and functional enrichment analyses for any sequenced genome of interest},
  author={Szklarczyk, Damian and others},
  journal={Nucleic Acids Research},
  year={2023}
}
```

**BioBERT**:
```bibtex
@article{biobert2020,
  title={BioBERT: a pre-trained biomedical language representation model for biomedical text mining},
  author={Lee, Jinhyuk and others},
  journal={Bioinformatics},
  year={2020}
}
```

**PyTorch Geometric**:
```bibtex
@inproceedings{pyg2019,
  title={Fast Graph Representation Learning with PyTorch Geometric},
  author={Fey, Matthias and Lenssen, Jan Eric},
  booktitle={ICLR Workshop on Representation Learning on Graphs and Manifolds},
  year={2019}
}
```

---

## Data Usage Policies

When using the integrated datasets:

1. **Respect licenses**: Follow individual dataset licenses
2. **Academic use**: Most datasets are free for academic research
3. **Commercial use**: Check specific licenses; some require permission
4. **Attribution**: Always cite original data sources
5. **Registration**: Some databases (e.g., DisGeNET) may require registration

---

## Disclaimer

This software is provided for research purposes only. It is not intended for clinical use or medical decision-making. The authors and contributors are not responsible for any consequences arising from the use of this software.

The integrated biomedical data is provided "as-is" from public sources. While efforts have been made to ensure data quality, users should verify critical information with original sources.
